raw <- read.csv('data.csv')                         #Import data
GCB <- raw[, -c(16:33,72)] %>%
    filter(age < 100 & VCL6 == 0 & VCL9 == 0 & VCL12 == 0) %>%
    select(-(VCL1:VCL16))
GCB[GCB == 0] <- NA                                 
GCB <- na.omit(GCB)                                 #Remove trashy data
n <- nrow(GCB)

GCB$age[GCB$age < 18] <- "juvenile"
GCB$age[GCB$age >= 18 & GCB$age < 35] <- "youth"
GCB$age[GCB$age >= 35 & GCB$age < 55] <- "midlife"
GCB$age[GCB$age >= 55] <- "elder"                   #Set age group

score <- GCB[, 1:15]
corr <- cor(score)                                  #Correlation of the scores
fa.parallel(corr, n.obs = n, n.iter = 100,
            main = "Scree plot with parallel analysis")
